{
  "answer": "In Cynewulf's *Elene*, Constantine sees the cross (described as the \"sign of the Savior’s Rood\" and \"victory-tree\") in a dream-vision on the eve of battle against a barbarian horde (Huns, Hreth-Goths, Franks, and Hugas) encamped across the Danube. A heavenly messenger appears to him, bearing the radiant cross-symbol inscribed with the words \"By this sign, conquer.\"[^1]\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [paragraphs](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-acdc07).\n\n[^2]: Cynewulf, *Elene*, [paragraphs](/works/cynewulf-elene-d2d132/01/translation/#p-306e06).",
